Despite being relieved as the head coach of the Super Eagles by the Nigerian Football Federation (NFF) last month, Gernot Rohr said he would cheer the team at the African Cup of Nations (AFCON). The German tactician told  NationSport that said there is no love lost between him and Nigerians adding that he misses the players and staff that were with him for more than five years in charge of the national team. Three-time AFCON Champions Nigeria begin their quest for a fourth title against the Pharaohs of Egypt today at the Roumdé Adjia Stadium in Garoua.    Senegal, Morocco in good start     Egypt’s Queiroz welcomes Nigeria tough challenge     Mahrez rallies Algeria for AFCON defence   “I am missing my team, my players and staff,” the ex-Bayern Munich defender said. “I would have loved to lead the team to this AFCON but it was not possible but I will support them from home.” - Advertisement - The former Gabon, Burkina Faso and Niger gaffer revealed he has been invited as a pundit at the AFCON for some sports channels for the later part of the month-long football extravaganza. “It is possible that I would come to the competition as a pundit during the last weeks of the competition,” he added.